Mechel, Polyus, Rosneft, X5 Group: Russian Equity Market Preview

-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 
2011-04-07T18:45:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/mechel-polyus-rosneft-x5-group-russian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 0.8 percent to 1,844.33 at
the close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index declined 1
percent to 2,089.52.  OAO  Mechel (MTLR)  :  Russia ’s largest producer of coal for
steelmaking will publish its first-quarter production results.
Company shares fell 1.5 percent to 889.50 rubles.  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX): Gold futures surged to a record
for a third straight day, advancing to $1,466.50 an ounce, after
the  European Central Bank  raised  interest rates  for the first
time in almost three years. Russia’s biggest gold producer added
0.3 percent to 1,717.8 rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): Crude oil rose above $110 a barrel
for the first time in 30 months with the contract for May
delivery touching $110.16 a barrel, the highest since Sept. 22,
2008. Shares of Russia’s biggest oil company fell 1.5 percent to
266.25 rubles.  X5 Retail Group NV (FIVE)  : Russia’s largest retailer
will publish its first-quarter sales and revenue trading update
at 10 a.m. in Moscow. The company’s global depositary receipts
fell 2.9 percent to $39.80 in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denis Maternovsky in Moscow at 
